## Staleness Detection

The document tracks which source files it was built from using a metadata comment:

```html
<!-- DOC-SYNC
  sources: content.js, popup.js, popup.html, popup.css, background.js, manifest.json
  generated: 2026-02-23T12:00:00Z
  source-hash: <sha256 of concatenated source files>
-->
```

### Sync Check Script (`scripts/doc-sync-check.js`)

A Node.js script that:
1. Reads the `DOC-SYNC` comment from the HTML doc
2. Hashes the current source files
3. Compares hashes — if different, prints a warning with which files changed
4. Exits with code 1 (stale) or 0 (up to date)

This script is called by the **post-commit git hook**.

---

## Git Hook Integration

### Post-commit hook (`.git/hooks/post-commit`)

After every commit:
1. Run the test suite (`node tests/test-all.js`)
2. Run the doc-sync check (`node scripts/doc-sync-check.js`)
3. If tests fail → print error (commit already happened, but warns developer)
4. If doc is stale → print warning with instructions to regenerate

### Pre-commit hook (`.git/hooks/pre-commit`)

Before every commit:
1. Run the test suite — if tests fail, **block the commit**
2. This ensures no broken code is committed

---

## When to Regenerate the Document

Regenerate `docs/how-it-works.html` when ANY of these change:

- A new section is added to a source file (new function, new feature)
- The data shape in storage changes (new fields)
- A new bug is discovered and fixed
- Architecture changes (new files, renamed components)
- The manifest version or permissions change
- Test count changes significantly

After regenerating, update the `DOC-SYNC` comment hash by running:
```bash
node scripts/doc-sync-check.js --update
```

---

## Checklist for Creating a New Explainer

- [ ] All 11 sections present and in order
- [ ] Hero stats match actual codebase metrics
- [ ] At least 2 interactive demos (input → output)
- [ ] All code blocks use syntax highlighting spans
- [ ] Navigation bar links to every section
- [ ] Active nav state updates on scroll
- [ ] Every architectural component has a consistent color
- [ ] Bug cards have before/after code
- [ ] Feature table is complete (cross-check with actual features)
- [ ] DOC-SYNC metadata comment is present
- [ ] `doc-sync-check.js` passes
- [ ] Document tested in browser (all demos functional)
